  "instructions": [
    "boil 4 cups of water in a large pot over high heat.",
    "place a large piece of aluminum foil or parchment paper on a flat surface and arrange 12 large lettuce leaves on it, overlapping them slightly.",
    "divide the beef brisket into thin strips and place them in a large bowl, adding the chopped lemongrass, galerang, galangal, kaffir lime leaves, garlic, ginger, fish sauce, lime juice, brown sugar, kaffir lime zest, turmeric, ground cumin, and salt. Mix well to combine.",
    "transfer the beef mixture to a separate bowl and set aside.",
    "in a small bowl, whisk together cornstarch, egg whites, and water until smooth. Add the coconut cream and mix until well combined.",
    "heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "add the chopped peanuts and cook, stirring frequently, until they are lightly toasted, about 2-3 minutes.",
    "add the grated ginger and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "add the lemongrass, galerang, galangal, and kaffir lime leaves and cook for 1 minute, stirring occasionally.",
    "add the beef brisket and cook, stirring frequently, until it is browned on all sides and cooked to your desired level of doneness, about 5-7 minutes.",
    "remove the beef from the skillet and transfer it to a plate.",
    "add the chopped scallions, bean sprouts, and sliced chilies to the skillet and cook, stirring frequently, until the vegetables are tender-crisp, about 3-5 minutes.",
    "add the cooked beef back to the skillet and stir to combine with the vegetables.",
    "add the lemongrass, galerang, galangal, and kaffir lime leaves and stir to combine.",
    "serving suggestion: place a large lettuce leaf on a flat surface and arrange 1/4 cup of the beef mixture in the center of the leaf. Fold the bottom half of the leaf up over the filling, then fold in the sides and roll the leaf into a tight cylinder. Repeat with the remaining beef mixture and lettuce leaves.",
    "steaming: place the steamer basket in a large pot and add 4 cups of water. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cover the pot with a lid.",
    "add the steamed jasmine rice to the steamer basket and cook for 5-7 minutes, or until heated through.",
    "add the fried shallots, basil leaves, sesame seeds, toasted coconut flakes, roasted sesame oil, korean chili flakes, corn, sliced red onion, black salt, and kaffir lime zest to the steamer basket and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes, or until the flavors are combined.",
    "meanwhile, cook the rice noodles according to the package instructions and set aside.",
    "to assemble the leaf wraps, place a large lettuce leaf on a flat surface and arrange 1/4 cup of the steamed jasmine rice mixture in the center of the leaf. Fold the bottom half of the leaf up over the filling, then fold in the sides and roll the leaf into a tight cylinder. Repeat with the remaining rice mixture and lettuce leaves.",
    "to serve, place a few of the leaf wraps on a plate and serve hot with the spicy sauce, pickled daikon, and fried shallots on the side.",
    "note: this recipe serves 4-6 people. adjust the ingredients as needed to feed your group.",
    "note: you can also use other types of leaf wraps, such as collard greens or kale, in place of the lettuce leaves.",
    "note: if you prefer a spicy sauce, you can add more cayenne pepper or chili flakes to taste.",
    "note: if you prefer a milder sauce, you can omit the cayenne pepper or chili flakes."
  ],
